2-form lattice gauge theory 



In the previous section, we have generalized the notions of category,
functor and natural transformation to the next level and we have seen
how one can construct explicit examples using Lie crossed modules. Let
us now generalize the ideas of Section  step by
step in order to obtain a higher level lattice gauge theory,
lattice -gauge theory , to be precise. Some key ideas of this
section are taken from  which deals with -categories
constructed from monoidal categories rather than from Lie -groups.


